args: Please come quickly, Your Highness!\nWe found a note from Eugene!
I'm going home. Thanks for everything.\n-Eugene
Home? He only got here yesterday!\nI wonder what changed his mind.
I know not, but we have searched the\ncastle grounds and he is not to be found.
Then we need to go after him.
I won't stop him if he wants to leave,\nbut if something is bothering him,\nI need to know what it is.
Of course, Your Highness.\nI shall rally the others at once.
...Hmm? You wanna know if I regret this?\nYeah, sticking around was never gonna fly.
I was never gonna become\nfriends with any of 'em...
Er, it's Eugene, right? From Quinbell?\nWhat brings you here?
I, um...just wanted to say thanks for\nhelping me out at the festival.
Also, I thought maybe I could say hi to\nfolks while I was here and...you know.
I mean, there's all kinds of people here,\nyeah? So I figured maybe at least one of\n'em might wanna...be my friend?
Are you really worried about that?\nBecause I think everyone here would\nbe happy to be your friend, Eugene.
Yeah, except I'm gloomy and cynical and\nmess up what I say when I'm nervous.\nIt's not exactly grade-A pal material.
I'm confident you'll find a lot\nof great friends here.
May I have a moment, Your Highness?
Of course. See you around, Eugene!
Man, that prince is something else.\nHe's got this crazy aura about him,\nand he clearly trusts all his friends.
So if he thinks I'm going to\nfind a friend here...
Oh, hey! Haven't seen you around before.\nYou new here, guy?
(C'mon, Eugene, get it together!\nTalk to him! Make a friend!)
You wanna come skate with me?
Oh man, you don't know how to skate?\nYou're gonna LOVE it! Look, just strap\nthese blades to your shoes, okay?
Ack! The ground just turned to ice!
Yeah, magic blades, blah blah blah.\nAnyway, let's get skating!
Oww... Man, I'm just one big bruise\nnow from falling all over the place.
What was even UP with that guy?\nHe just yammered on about skating\nand didn't listen to a word I said!
Umm... Are you talking to me?
(Ugh, not again... Wait, no. I can't let that\nlast failure put me off the entire idea of\nmaking friends—I can do this!)
I, um... See, I just came here, sooo...
Uh oh. Someone's got a case of the sads.\nWell, I know just the thing to turn that\nfrown manically upside down: DANCING!
Wh-what? H-hang on! Dancing's really not\nmy thing!
Don't worry, I'll teach you everything.\nReady? Aaand...step! Turn! Step!\nLeap! Pirouette! GRAND JETÉ!
I told you I'm no good at—GYAAAAA!
Okay, why is everyone in that stupid castle\nso full of stupid energy?

I mean, yeah, they all seemed happy
to have me around, and it was kind of
fun, but... I can't deal with folks who
are that...cheerful.
Heh. I'm conflicted all right, buddy.
But if I run away now, it'll be exactly\nthe same as all my other failures.
Thanks, Sam. Your support means a lot.
All right. I'm gonna do this. If I want to\nmake friends and have a youth I can look\nback on without regret, I have to change.
I need to stop hanging around in shadows\nand step into the light! ...Or whatever.
Oh man, they actually followed me!\nOkay, time to be strong and—
(Nope. A thousand years of trying won't\nbe enough for me to get along with him.)
If it's friends you want, I'm your man.\nSo hop on my chariot and let's RIDE,\ndaddy-o! Yeeeeee-haw!
What the heck are you SAYING, gosh?!
Hop on my partner and ride, baby!\nWe're gonna be INVINCIBLE!
Okay, what is WITH this guy?
My chariot is the BEST, baby!\nLet's go 'cause some trouble!
Aw, don't be a square! Be a BOSS!
(I was stupid to think I could change\nmyself. I'm gonna be awkward forever...)
